From: Andrew Davis <afd@ti.com>
Date: Mon, 10 Jun 2024 09:28:36 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] power: reset: brcmstb: Do not go into infinite loop if reset fails
Git-commit: cf8c39b00e982fa506b16f9d76657838c09150cb
Patch-mainline: v6.12-rc1
References: stable-fixes

There may be other backup reset methods available, do not halt
here so that other reset methods can be tried.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Davis <afd@ti.com>
Reviewed-by: Dhruva Gole <d-gole@ti.com>
Acked-by: Florian Fainelli <florian.fainelli@broadcom.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20240610142836.168603-5-afd@ti.com
Signed-off-by: Sebastian Reichel <sebastian.reichel@collabora.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/power/reset/brcmstb-reboot.c | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/power/reset/brcmstb-reboot.c b/drivers/power/reset/brcmstb-reboot.c
index 0524ee53d6ba..b9c093f6064c 100644
--- a/drivers/power/reset/brcmstb-reboot.c
+++ b/drivers/power/reset/brcmstb-reboot.c
@@ -58,9 +58,6 @@ static int brcmstb_restart_handler(struct sys_off_data *data)
 		return NOTIFY_DONE;
 	}
 
-	while (1)
-		;
-
 	return NOTIFY_DONE;
 }
 
